usage: git select [<options>] [<sku>]

Select SKU (checkout branch that matches bundle branch)

    -h|--help               display help
    -q|--quiet              don't print submodule name when selecting
    -e|--stop-on-error      stop looping as soon as command fails (exit code != 0)
    -a|--all                select all submodules (ignore SKU filter)
    -j<n>                   number of submodules selected in parallel (default to 16)
    --dev                   force selection of development branches
    --prod                  force selection of last published version
                            if a dev branch points at the vtag, activate it
    .                       do not traverse submodules
    <sku>                   SKU to be selected (default to bundle active branch)
    
example:
    git select              # select current SKU 
    git select sku/sal/dev  # select dev branch of sal SKU
    git select --prod       # select last published version on current SKU
    git select --prod .     # switch to prod branch of current SKU in current module only